	(text "This is the most critical part of the build. Read before soldering.\n\nBATTERY: Single cell 3.7V LiPo only. No multi-cellpacks. Use a\npack with built in protection circuit (pretty much all LiPo's have\nthis, unless you buy raw cells).\n\nVSYS ONLY: Connect OUT+ to VSYS (pin 39) only, never to VBUS\nor 3.3V. The Pico W has a built in buck-boost regulator on\nVSYS that handles the full LiPo range (3.0-4.2V). Bypassing\nit causes voltage sag and damage.\n\nVOLTAGE DIVIDER (100k+100k resistors): REQUIRED. Do not skip.\nThe ADC on GP28 has a 3.3V maximum. A full LiPo is 4.2V which\nwill permanetely destroy the ADC pin if connected directly.\nThe divider halves this to a safe 2.1V maximum. Before\nconnecting to GP28, measure the midpoint with a multimeter and\nconfirm it reads roughly half the battery voltage.\n\nTP4056: Connect B+ and B- to the battery only.Default charge\ncurrent is 1A, suitable for 1000mAh+ packs. (if you use one\nunder, make sure it can handle charging at above 1C, or\nequivalent based on your mAh, search this up).\n\nSee WIRING.md for full details.\n\nCopyright (C) 2026 Phillip Rødseth / Kjern.no"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 119.634 145.796 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.016 1.016)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "5d35a4de-035e-40b4-9e3f-bf5870444c6f")
	)
